# Git Commits

When creating or amending git commits in this repo:

- **Never** add `Co-authored-by` lines (including `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`).
- Use a single-line or short multi-line message with **only** the commit subject/body the user requested.
- If amending or rewriting history to remove co-author trailers, do not reintroduce them.

Example — correct:

```
Release v1.0.2 — add unit test suite.
```

Example — do **not** use:

```
Release v1.0.2 — add unit test suite.

Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>
```
